.TH MLWORKS 1 1997-10-06 Harlequin MLWORKS
.SH NAME
mlworks-basis \- MLWorks incremental compiler with Standard 
.RS 16
ML Basis library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mlworks-basis
[
.BI \-mono
]
.RB [ " \-gui " ]
.RB [ " \-tty " ]
.RB [ " \-debug-mode " ]
.if n .ti +1.45i
.RB [ " \-optimize-mode " ]
.RB [ " \-no-init " ]
.RB [ " \-silent " ]
.if n .ti +1.45i
.RB [ " \-stack " \fIn\fP\   ]
.RB [ " \-help " ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
.B mlworks-basis
invokes the MLWorks system as an interactive incremental
compiler with a GUI and programming tools.  It is exactly the same as 
.B mlworks
but it additionally provides a ready-to-use copy of the Standard ML Basis
library.  
.LP
.B mlworks-basis
is a shell script which invokes
.BR mlrun (1)
on an ML image containing the incremental compiler, GUI, and Standard
ML Basis library.
.LP
See 
.BR mlworks (1)
for more information on the 
.B mlworks-basis
script itself, and the
.I MLWorks User Guide
for a full description of the interactive environment.
.SH FILES
.PD 0
.LP
.B $IMAGEDIR/guib.img
.LP
.RS 4
The interactive MLWorks image with X Window System and Motif GUI
environment, and the Standard ML Basis library.
.PD
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mlworks (1),
.BR mlrun (1),
.BR mlimage (1),
.BR mlpervasive (1),
.BR mlbatch (1)
.LP
.I MLWorks User Guide
